cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.IT

This paper deals with sensor selection in a linear dynamical system, which is a problem in control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also uses randomized sampling algorithms and derives lower bounds, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves numerical computations and optimization, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
